This product does not bundle third-party data. At runtime, on the operator's
explicit command (e.g. `ariadne update-intel`, `ariadne atm-sync`), it fetches
attribution and market data from the public, keyless sources listed below. Each
source is governed by its own licence and terms of use. You are responsible for
complying with them, especially before redistributing any derived dataset.

================================================================================
Attribution / label data
================================================================================

* OFAC Specially Designated Nationals (SDN) list
  U.S. Department of the Treasury — U.S. Government work (public domain).
  Consumed directly (sdn.xml) and via the 0xB10C mirror
  "ofac-sanctioned-digital-currency-addresses".

* etherscan-labels — github.com/brianleect/etherscan-labels
  Public Etherscan address labels. MIT-licensed repository.
  Used to name exchanges/DEX/DeFi/bridges/mixers/ATMs and issuer-frozen addresses.

* ethereum-lists darklist — github.com/MyEtherWallet/ethereum-lists
  Community scam/phishing darklist. MIT-licensed repository.

* ScamSniffer scam-database — github.com/scamsniffer/scam-database
  Community scam/phishing address blacklist.

* Ransomwhere — ransomwhe.re
  Crowdsourced ransomware payment addresses (published under CC0).

================================================================================
Physical-location intelligence
================================================================================

* OpenStreetMap, via the Overpass API — openstreetmap.org / overpass-api.de
  © OpenStreetMap contributors. Data available under the Open Database Licence
  (ODbL) 1.0; cartography under CC BY-SA. Crypto-ATM operator and kiosk
  locations are derived from OSM `amenity=atm` / crypto tags. If you redistribute
  ATM data derived from this, you must attribute OpenStreetMap and comply with
  the ODbL.

================================================================================
Market / FX data (fiat valuation)
================================================================================

* Binance public market data (klines) — binance.com
  Historical daily-close prices. Subject to Binance's API terms of use.

* Frankfurter / European Central Bank reference rates — frankfurter.app
  EUR foreign-exchange reference rates published by the ECB.

================================================================================
On-chain data providers
================================================================================

* Blockstream Esplora (Bitcoin) — blockstream.info
* Blockscout (Ethereum + EVM L2s, Etherscan-compatible API) — blockscout.com
* TronScan (Tron TRC-20) — tronscan.org

Each is queried through its documented public API. For operational security and
to avoid disclosing investigative targets to third parties, route queries through
Tor (ARIADNE_PROXY) or a self-hosted indexer (ARIADNE_ENDPOINT_<CHAIN>).

